1
00:00:00,586 --> 00:00:02,585
[HELICOPTER BLADES WHIRRING]

2
00:00:06,094 --> 00:00:08,423
MEREDITH: A painful irony for doctors

3
00:00:08,423 --> 00:00:10,173
is that we often have to make you sicker

4
00:00:10,173 --> 00:00:11,882
in order to heal you.

5
00:00:11,884 --> 00:00:13,333
Megan?

6
00:00:16,155 --> 00:00:17,236
Megan.

7
00:00:20,594 --> 00:00:22,513
Who... Who are you?

8
00:00:27,224 --> 00:00:30,053
Sorry. [LAUGHS] I had to do it.

9
00:00:30,053 --> 00:00:31,092
[BOTH LAUGH]

10
00:00:31,117 --> 00:00:32,448
Will you unstrap me from this thing

11
00:00:32,450 --> 00:00:34,323
so I can hug your
ridiculously pale body?

12
00:00:34,325 --> 00:00:35,451
Yeah.

13
00:00:35,829 --> 00:00:37,159
[BELT CLICKS]

14
00:00:37,640 --> 00:00:38,640
Come here.

15
00:00:39,975 --> 00:00:43,316
If a bone has healed unevenly,
we have to rebreak it.

16
00:00:44,539 --> 00:00:46,347
If a scar is too thick,

17
00:00:46,347 --> 00:00:49,561
we have to scrape it off
and create a new wound.

18
00:00:53,594 --> 00:00:55,875
We break you down to rebuild you.

19
00:00:58,418 --> 00:01:00,338
MEGAN: I was not kept in that hole.

20
00:01:00,338 --> 00:01:03,207
I was tossed in the hole
when the bombing started.

21
00:01:03,209 --> 00:01:05,128
They were trying to protect me.

22
00:01:05,129 --> 00:01:07,787
Trauma surgeons aren't
easy to come by in Iraq.

23
00:01:07,789 --> 00:01:10,263
- So all these years, you...
- I was treated really well.

24
00:01:10,507 --> 00:01:12,787
They'd just, you know,
kill me if I left.

25
00:01:12,789 --> 00:01:14,459
Your wife is really pretty.

26
00:01:14,897 --> 00:01:16,168
I'm really happy to meet you.

27
00:01:16,168 --> 00:01:18,289
Me too. [CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

28
00:01:21,811 --> 00:01:23,545
Hey, stranger. [CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

29
00:01:24,341 --> 00:01:25,718
[SOBBING]

30
00:01:27,879 --> 00:01:29,578
[INHALES SHARPLY]

31
00:01:29,579 --> 00:01:31,045
I'm so sorry.

32
00:01:31,625 --> 00:01:34,656
Shh. Babe, it's okay.
It's okay. I'm okay.

33
00:01:34,739 --> 00:01:35,888
I'm...

34
00:01:35,912 --> 00:01:37,322
Okay, ow.

35
00:01:37,347 --> 00:01:38,426
You're gonna have to... Ow.

36
00:01:38,759 --> 00:01:40,383
- What hurts?
- What's wrong?

37
00:01:40,408 --> 00:01:42,228
There was a bombing six months ago.

38
00:01:42,253 --> 00:01:44,539
I... took some shrapnel.

39
00:01:44,563 --> 00:01:46,147
There were post-op complications.

40
00:01:46,173 --> 00:01:48,500
It didn't heal so well.

41
00:01:50,313 --> 00:01:51,313
♪♪

42
00:02:01,093 --> 00:02:04,802
Okay. Um, all right, everyone!
Listen up, please!

43
00:02:05,296 --> 00:02:07,302
Uh, first, I want to thank you all

44
00:02:07,304 --> 00:02:09,842
for keeping your heads
during the events of last night.

45
00:02:09,843 --> 00:02:13,923
Thanks to you, there were
very minimal injuries,

46
00:02:13,924 --> 00:02:16,920
and the firefighters were able
to contain the blaze quickly.

47
00:02:16,937 --> 00:02:21,106
There was some damage, however,
that will need to be repaired.

48
00:02:21,600 --> 00:02:26,389
Uh, the neuro ICU, the cath lab,
and pulmonary clinic...

49
00:02:26,413 --> 00:02:27,656
[CLEARS THROAT]

50
00:02:27,818 --> 00:02:29,475
[HUSHED VOICE] She fired Eliza.

51
00:02:29,687 --> 00:02:30,977
[HUSHED VOICE] Oh, yeah. I heard.

52
00:02:30,978 --> 00:02:33,227
Just give her some room.
Getting fired is humiliating.

53
00:02:33,228 --> 00:02:34,477
How much room?

54
00:02:34,478 --> 00:02:36,396
Like, hours or days?

55
00:02:36,397 --> 00:02:38,106
<i>...and endoscopy suites...</i>

56
00:02:38,108 --> 00:02:39,875
I've never been fired.

57
00:02:40,108 --> 00:02:42,825
<i>These stations will be off-limits
to pedestrian foot traffic.</i>

58
00:02:42,826 --> 00:02:44,356
Stephanie's gone.

59
00:02:44,358 --> 00:02:47,281
She was airlifted to
a burn center in Texas.

60
00:02:48,897 --> 00:02:50,646
<i>So until further notice,</i>

61
00:02:50,647 --> 00:02:53,632
ORs 3 through 6 are nonfunctional.

62
00:02:53,656 --> 00:02:55,100
Hunt, your sister's here?

63
00:02:55,126 --> 00:02:56,927
Yeah, Riggs is taking her to CT.

64
00:02:56,929 --> 00:02:59,616
Uh, Riggs and I, we're gonna
need to take some leave.

65
00:02:59,641 --> 00:03:01,734
Understood. I'll update Bailey.

66
00:03:02,098 --> 00:03:03,888
Uh, your sister will be
our first priority

67
00:03:03,889 --> 00:03:05,807
- as soon as we're done here.
- Okay. Thanks.

68
00:03:05,808 --> 00:03:10,022
To recap, we are to avoid
ORs 3 through 6

69
00:03:10,048 --> 00:03:13,078
and the entire neuro wing,
as they are unstable.

70
00:03:13,429 --> 00:03:14,717
[CLATTER]

71
00:03:14,718 --> 00:03:16,288
[INDISTINCT SHOUTING]

72
00:03:20,754 --> 00:03:23,837
And also avoid
fourth-floor nurses station

73
00:03:23,862 --> 00:03:25,420
until further notice.

74
00:03:27,372 --> 00:03:30,522
synced by susinz
*www.addic7ed.com*

75
00:03:34,269 --> 00:03:35,397
[TELEPHONE RINGS]

76
00:03:36,968 --> 00:03:37,764
Hey.

77
00:03:37,789 --> 00:03:39,835
- Hey.
- You're working?

78
00:03:40,135 --> 00:03:41,788
Yeah, I'm gonna work.

79
00:03:43,953 --> 00:03:45,152
How's Megan?

80
00:03:45,481 --> 00:03:47,194
Uh, she's alive.

81
00:03:47,663 --> 00:03:49,192
And... well, not quite well,

82
00:03:49,192 --> 00:03:52,991
but she's funny and sharp
and very much alive,

83
00:03:52,992 --> 00:03:55,085
which is, you know, energizing.

84
00:03:55,225 --> 00:03:58,151
I mean, this miracle happened,
and it makes me aware

85
00:03:58,152 --> 00:04:00,651
that I have the ability
to make that miracle happen

86
00:04:00,652 --> 00:04:03,532
for someone else's family, so... yeah.

87
00:04:03,532 --> 00:04:04,764
I'm gonna work.

88
00:04:05,676 --> 00:04:07,569
You don't think
you should be with Owen today?

89
00:04:07,862 --> 00:04:09,651
You know what...
I'm super-good in a crisis,

90
00:04:09,652 --> 00:04:11,074
but the crisis is over.

91
00:04:11,460 --> 00:04:12,460
[CABINET DOOR CLOSES]

92
00:04:16,452 --> 00:04:17,709
[DOOR CLOSES]

93
00:04:17,709 --> 00:04:18,757
[WHIRRING]

94
00:04:18,887 --> 00:04:20,807
And you've been here for how long?

95
00:04:21,560 --> 00:04:23,242
Couple years now.

96
00:04:24,577 --> 00:04:27,093
And have you met anyone...

97
00:04:27,605 --> 00:04:29,314
you know, significant?

98
00:04:30,572 --> 00:04:31,572
Hey.

99
00:04:31,598 --> 00:04:33,307
Oh, h-hang one sec, Meg.

100
00:04:33,737 --> 00:04:35,031
- Hey.
- Hey.

101
00:04:35,033 --> 00:04:36,452
How is she doing?

102
00:04:36,930 --> 00:04:40,444
Oh, she's, um, got
a frozen abdomen, but...

103
00:04:41,653 --> 00:04:45,031
You know, all things considered,
she's pretty okay.

104
00:04:45,033 --> 00:04:46,398
That's great.

105
00:04:46,750 --> 00:04:47,920
And how are you?

106
00:04:48,473 --> 00:04:51,406
Yeah, all things considered,
pretty okay.

107
00:04:52,704 --> 00:04:54,312
- You?
- Same.

108
00:05:01,735 --> 00:05:04,024
Hey, sorry, Meg. Where were we?

109
00:05:04,952 --> 00:05:06,362
I was asking if you met anyone,

110
00:05:06,362 --> 00:05:08,430
and you were buying time to come
up with an acceptable answer.

111
00:05:08,454 --> 00:05:10,452
- I wasn't buying time.
- Liar.

112
00:05:10,803 --> 00:05:11,952
Look. Uh...

113
00:05:12,771 --> 00:05:14,481
I-I did meet someone.

114
00:05:16,117 --> 00:05:17,218
And?

115
00:05:17,362 --> 00:05:19,507
And... she's not you.

116
00:05:21,742 --> 00:05:22,795
Smooth.

117
00:05:24,077 --> 00:05:26,007
- Right?
- [BOTH LAUGH]

118
00:05:26,461 --> 00:05:28,670
The southwest wing of the
second floor has been cleared,

119
00:05:28,670 --> 00:05:31,139
so all of the patients
in beds 3 through 10

120
00:05:31,163 --> 00:05:32,576
can be transported back upstairs, okay?

121
00:05:32,600 --> 00:05:34,920
- DeLuca, what do you got?
- Beau Martinez, 14 years old.

122
00:05:34,920 --> 00:05:36,250
Presents with intense jaw pain

123
00:05:36,250 --> 00:05:37,509
and recurrent left-sided headaches.

124
00:05:37,511 --> 00:05:39,202
Beau, can you follow my finger?

125
00:05:39,257 --> 00:05:40,334
Good.

126
00:05:40,420 --> 00:05:42,050
- When did the pain start?
- A few months ago.

127
00:05:42,050 --> 00:05:44,379
They took these X-rays
last month. They saw nothing.

128
00:05:44,380 --> 00:05:45,750
They gave him pain pills
that don't work,

129
00:05:45,750 --> 00:05:47,459
and now they won't give him
any more 'cause...

130
00:05:47,461 --> 00:05:49,500
They treat him like he's
a drug addict or something.

131
00:05:49,872 --> 00:05:51,129
That's not my kid.

132
00:05:51,130 --> 00:05:52,959
He can't even play baseball anymore.

133
00:05:52,961 --> 00:05:56,108
He says it's a stabbing pain
in the jaw and mastoid area.

134
00:05:56,187 --> 00:05:59,398
Thought maybe we should get
a head, cervical, maxillofacial CT.

135
00:05:59,423 --> 00:06:00,461
Agreed.

136
00:06:00,487 --> 00:06:02,367
Beau, I've got you.

137
00:06:02,375 --> 00:06:04,213
I know this pain is real,
and I am not gonna rest

138
00:06:04,214 --> 00:06:06,778
until we find out what it is
and how to fix it.

139
00:06:06,803 --> 00:06:08,333
You have my word. You both do.

140
00:06:08,358 --> 00:06:09,449
Okay.

141
00:06:15,014 --> 00:06:17,209
- Is this Megan Hunt?
- Yeah.

142
00:06:17,380 --> 00:06:19,673
Nastiest abdominal wound I've ever seen.

143
00:06:19,675 --> 00:06:22,124
Massive hernia, giant fistula.

144
00:06:22,125 --> 00:06:25,463
The abdominal layers have
scarred and fused to each other.

145
00:06:25,906 --> 00:06:28,064
Her small bowel and colon are just...

146
00:06:28,065 --> 00:06:29,194
One big blob.

147
00:06:29,220 --> 00:06:31,314
And there's not enough healthy skin

148
00:06:31,315 --> 00:06:32,812
to properly close the wound.

149
00:06:32,836 --> 00:06:34,654
I think we just optimize her nutrition,

150
00:06:34,656 --> 00:06:35,944
vac the wound, and wait.

151
00:06:35,946 --> 00:06:37,382
I mean, it'll close eventually.

152
00:06:37,406 --> 00:06:40,156
She wants us to reverse the colostomy.

153
00:06:40,180 --> 00:06:42,350
I can't see a way to make that happen.

154
00:06:42,560 --> 00:06:43,709
Well, I can.

155
00:06:43,918 --> 00:06:45,303
And you taught it to me.

156
00:06:50,454 --> 00:06:53,225
So, I would like to
reapproximate the abdominal wall

157
00:06:53,610 --> 00:06:54,952
a little bit at a time.

158
00:06:54,978 --> 00:06:57,569
Put in tissue expanders
to stretch the skin

159
00:06:57,595 --> 00:06:59,913
and then pull the abdomen
back together slowly.

160
00:06:59,939 --> 00:07:01,478
And then we'll go back in,

161
00:07:01,538 --> 00:07:04,497
take down the fistula,
reverse the colostomy,

162
00:07:04,499 --> 00:07:07,288
and I'll close with
a component separation surgery.

163
00:07:07,288 --> 00:07:08,497
Which means what?

164
00:07:08,499 --> 00:07:10,577
Which means
she's my new favorite person.

165
00:07:10,579 --> 00:07:13,077
Who are you? I'm Meredith Grey.

166
00:07:13,079 --> 00:07:14,944
Thank you for your service, Dr. Hunt.

167
00:07:14,970 --> 00:07:17,497
Well, I admit I've been
out of the O.R. for a while,

168
00:07:17,499 --> 00:07:19,788
but this sounds like a risky surgery.

169
00:07:19,788 --> 00:07:21,457
BAILEY: It most definitely is.

170
00:07:21,459 --> 00:07:23,288
And there's no guarantee
that it'll work.

171
00:07:23,288 --> 00:07:25,127
Yeah, which is why Dr. Bailey and I

172
00:07:25,129 --> 00:07:27,952
would recommend
a more conservative approach.

173
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:30,497
Thank you, but I just came back
from being presumed dead.

174
00:07:30,499 --> 00:07:32,084
I'm not about to play it safe.

175
00:07:35,014 --> 00:07:37,132
Also, it's really hard

176
00:07:37,156 --> 00:07:39,483
to live with an open
abdominal wound in Iraq.

177
00:07:39,538 --> 00:07:41,207
What do you mean, "in Iraq"?

178
00:07:41,356 --> 00:07:42,398
[SIGHS]

179
00:07:43,141 --> 00:07:45,404
Yeah, I was trying to figure out
how to tell you this.

180
00:07:45,430 --> 00:07:47,959
As soon as I'm well,
I have to go back to Iraq.

181
00:07:50,528 --> 00:07:51,957
My child is there.

182
00:07:52,178 --> 00:07:53,312
♪♪

183
00:08:01,187 --> 00:08:04,692
His name is Farouk. His parents
were Syrian insurgent fighters.

184
00:08:04,718 --> 00:08:06,108
They both died in combat.

185
00:08:06,291 --> 00:08:08,889
I took him in when he was 4.
He's 10 now.

186
00:08:09,595 --> 00:08:11,156
I'm the only parent he has,

187
00:08:11,180 --> 00:08:14,264
and he is the main reason that
I stayed sane all these years.

188
00:08:14,547 --> 00:08:15,875
I'm a grandmother?

189
00:08:15,877 --> 00:08:16,709
[LAUGHS]

190
00:08:16,826 --> 00:08:18,110
And you couldn't bring him with you?

191
00:08:18,134 --> 00:08:19,593
You're a national hero.

192
00:08:19,617 --> 00:08:21,600
Tell that to the U.S. immigration laws.

193
00:08:22,983 --> 00:08:26,389
If your surgery works,
I'll have a functioning bowel?

194
00:08:26,468 --> 00:08:27,627
That's the plan.

195
00:08:27,762 --> 00:08:28,932
Then that's what we're doing.

196
00:08:34,177 --> 00:08:36,303
[WOMAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY ON P.A.]

197
00:08:36,866 --> 00:08:37,881
Meredith?

198
00:08:38,625 --> 00:08:40,203
I'm sorry... I would
never have asked you

199
00:08:40,205 --> 00:08:41,975
to consult on Megan's case.

200
00:08:42,015 --> 00:08:43,350
Oh, you didn't ask me.

201
00:08:44,195 --> 00:08:47,084
Well, is you working on Megan
the best idea?

202
00:08:47,085 --> 00:08:49,043
I mean, family and all,
conflict of interest.

203
00:08:49,044 --> 00:08:50,241
She's not my family.

204
00:08:51,609 --> 00:08:53,043
[HUSHED VOICE] Well, I get that, but...

205
00:08:53,044 --> 00:08:54,874
I am the best person for this job.

206
00:08:54,875 --> 00:08:56,182
Just let me help.

207
00:08:58,745 --> 00:09:00,921
[WOMAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY ON P.A.]

208
00:09:03,966 --> 00:09:05,639
Are you crying about the empty board?

209
00:09:05,948 --> 00:09:07,648
Did you see Steph last night?

210
00:09:07,996 --> 00:09:09,673
Oh. Um, yeah.

211
00:09:09,876 --> 00:09:10,956
Yeah, look, we...

212
00:09:10,980 --> 00:09:13,610
She was hurt, but we got to her in time.

213
00:09:13,729 --> 00:09:16,575
It was kind of unbelievable.
I mean, it was, uh...

214
00:09:17,335 --> 00:09:19,453
It was thrilling, actually.

215
00:09:19,455 --> 00:09:21,139
You know? It was a rush.

216
00:09:21,164 --> 00:09:22,741
Who am I gonna talk to now?

217
00:09:22,767 --> 00:09:24,687
Who am I gonna compete against?

218
00:09:24,711 --> 00:09:26,711
W-Who's gonna tell me
when I'm being ridiculous

219
00:09:26,735 --> 00:09:29,171
or... or when I stink and need a shower?

220
00:09:29,196 --> 00:09:31,412
Way to make Stephanie's life-changing
injuries about you.

221
00:09:31,436 --> 00:09:33,725
You called it a rush!

222
00:09:35,250 --> 00:09:36,408
Yeah, I guess.

223
00:09:36,409 --> 00:09:37,959
Oh, and, uh, you do.

224
00:09:37,960 --> 00:09:39,038
Do what?

225
00:09:39,039 --> 00:09:40,369
Need a shower.

226
00:09:40,370 --> 00:09:41,491
[SCOFFS]

227
00:09:42,289 --> 00:09:44,576
- Hey.
- Oh. Hey.

228
00:09:44,577 --> 00:09:45,682
You busy?

229
00:09:45,683 --> 00:09:47,796
Uh, have you seen the board?

230
00:09:48,265 --> 00:09:49,515
Come with me.

231
00:09:55,783 --> 00:09:57,046
Hey, looking good, Max.

232
00:09:57,071 --> 00:09:58,779
Feeling good, Dr. Alex.

233
00:09:58,923 --> 00:10:00,921
- Hey, Max, this is, uh, Dr. Wilson.
- Hi.

234
00:10:00,946 --> 00:10:02,530
She's gonna read me your chart, okay?

235
00:10:03,758 --> 00:10:05,945
Max Spencer, 7 years old.

236
00:10:05,970 --> 00:10:09,129
Has had intermittent abdominal
pain and vomiting for months.

237
00:10:09,153 --> 00:10:11,113
Upper GI found evidence of malrotation

238
00:10:11,138 --> 00:10:12,875
due to the presence of bands.

239
00:10:12,956 --> 00:10:16,562
Needs a Ladd's procedure,
which is scheduled for...

240
00:10:16,586 --> 00:10:19,366
As soon my gastric emptying
study comes back normal.

241
00:10:19,519 --> 00:10:21,109
[LAUGHS] Exactly.

242
00:10:21,366 --> 00:10:23,398
Wow. You're pretty smart, huh?

243
00:10:25,409 --> 00:10:26,585
♪♪

244
00:10:28,913 --> 00:10:29,913
Look!

245
00:10:30,610 --> 00:10:33,500
Allora the Warrior Queen! Is that you?!

246
00:10:35,743 --> 00:10:37,613
Max, don't blow her cover.

247
00:10:38,647 --> 00:10:40,225
She's gonna be doing your surgery.

248
00:10:41,539 --> 00:10:42,717
♪♪

249
00:10:46,383 --> 00:10:47,460
Uh...

250
00:10:48,907 --> 00:10:50,100
Are you serious?

251
00:10:50,398 --> 00:10:52,806
You're gonna let me do
a Ladd's procedure? By myself?

252
00:10:52,807 --> 00:10:54,062
Think you can handle it?

253
00:10:54,124 --> 00:10:56,792
Handle it? I'm a frickin' warrior queen!

254
00:10:56,885 --> 00:10:58,038
[CHUCKLES]

255
00:11:00,096 --> 00:11:01,335
♪♪

256
00:11:02,767 --> 00:11:04,600
[CELLPHONES BUZZING, CHIMING]

257
00:11:06,807 --> 00:11:08,437
- You paged?
- Sub-I's.

258
00:11:08,875 --> 00:11:10,202
[CLEARS THROAT] What?

259
00:11:10,227 --> 00:11:12,639
As if we didn't have
enough to deal with today,

