521
00:20:53,434 --> 00:20:55,085
No. No, your face is perfect.

522
00:20:56,720 --> 00:20:57,827
I mean...

523
00:20:58,382 --> 00:21:00,241
I... have to... I have a...

524
00:21:00,486 --> 00:21:01,565
What's that?

525
00:21:01,589 --> 00:21:03,772
This was great, but I have, uh...

526
00:21:04,219 --> 00:21:05,436
[CLEARS THROAT]

527
00:21:08,528 --> 00:21:11,487
♪ Ooh-ooh, I'm a rebel
just for kicks, now ♪

528
00:21:11,511 --> 00:21:14,641
♪ I been feelin' it since 1986, now ♪

529
00:21:14,665 --> 00:21:17,444
♪ Might be over now,
but I feel it still ♪

530
00:21:17,631 --> 00:21:18,750
Can you hear me?

531
00:21:19,750 --> 00:21:20,905
Yeah.

532
00:21:21,039 --> 00:21:22,949
I don't think you should be up there.

533
00:21:22,973 --> 00:21:24,030
Why not?

534
00:21:24,056 --> 00:21:26,647
Because what you are about to
see is decidedly unsexy.

535
00:21:26,673 --> 00:21:28,375
Blood... guts.

536
00:21:28,788 --> 00:21:30,248
Nah, you look good in anything.

537
00:21:30,272 --> 00:21:31,813
[LAUGHING] Shut up.

538
00:21:33,326 --> 00:21:34,890
- Hi.
- Hi.

539
00:21:34,914 --> 00:21:36,772
Do you have any questions
before we get started?

540
00:21:36,797 --> 00:21:38,819
- Can I see the expanders?
- Of course.

541
00:21:38,845 --> 00:21:40,080
Bokhee?

542
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:43,788
Wow! That is... Wow. That's big.

543
00:21:44,182 --> 00:21:45,827
We'll deflate them to put them in,

544
00:21:45,853 --> 00:21:48,102
and then we will slowly
reinflate them with saline.

545
00:21:48,126 --> 00:21:50,147
We're gonna need as much space
as we can get.

546
00:21:50,237 --> 00:21:51,759
You know what we'd say
in the Army right now?

547
00:21:51,784 --> 00:21:52,772
What?

548
00:21:52,798 --> 00:21:54,601
- Say it with me, Nathan!
- Mm.

549
00:21:54,987 --> 00:21:56,108
- Hooah!
- Hooah!

550
00:21:56,134 --> 00:21:57,084
- Hooah!
- Hooah!

551
00:21:57,108 --> 00:21:58,671
- Hooah!
- Hooah!

552
00:21:59,195 --> 00:22:00,819
Let's do this thing, Dr. Grey.

553
00:22:00,845 --> 00:22:01,780
Let's do it.

554
00:22:01,806 --> 00:22:02,806
Okay.

555
00:22:02,962 --> 00:22:04,210
[MONITOR BEEPING]

556
00:22:07,638 --> 00:22:09,798
[WOMAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY ON P.A.]

557
00:22:09,876 --> 00:22:11,957
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

558
00:22:15,213 --> 00:22:16,476
[HYPERVENTILATING]

559
00:22:19,125 --> 00:22:20,503
Okay, all right.

560
00:22:20,505 --> 00:22:21,515
Okay.

561
00:22:21,954 --> 00:22:24,203
All right. Look. Hey.

562
00:22:24,204 --> 00:22:26,913
This is a minor surgery. She'll be fine.

563
00:22:26,914 --> 00:22:28,491
This stage is nothing.

564
00:22:29,086 --> 00:22:30,553
[BREATHING RAPIDLY]

565
00:22:30,694 --> 00:22:31,794
All right. You know what?

566
00:22:31,795 --> 00:22:33,835
You... You need to put your head
between your knees.

567
00:22:34,250 --> 00:22:35,147
No.

568
00:22:35,173 --> 00:22:37,154
Head between your knees, Major!

569
00:22:38,207 --> 00:22:39,207
Sit down.

570
00:22:39,270 --> 00:22:40,554
[BREATHING RAPIDLY]

571
00:22:42,302 --> 00:22:44,436
All right. That's it.
All right. Breathe.

572
00:22:47,108 --> 00:22:49,429
I can't lose her again, Teddy.

573
00:22:49,738 --> 00:22:50,896
I know.

574
00:22:50,922 --> 00:22:52,171
I lost 10 years.

575
00:22:52,233 --> 00:22:54,061
She doesn't even look
the way I remember her.

576
00:22:54,086 --> 00:22:56,210
I lost her even in my memory.

577
00:22:56,780 --> 00:22:58,155
And now she's back.

578
00:23:00,068 --> 00:23:01,857
And I can't lose her again.

579
00:23:01,883 --> 00:23:03,673
I know. It's okay.

580
00:23:05,210 --> 00:23:07,749
Listen, you have a plane to catch.

581
00:23:07,773 --> 00:23:09,171
I'm not going anywhere.

582
00:23:12,244 --> 00:23:13,491
[BREATHING SLOWLY]

583
00:23:14,108 --> 00:23:15,226
♪♪

584
00:23:23,938 --> 00:23:25,817
[POUNDING, DRILLS WHIRRING]

585
00:23:27,576 --> 00:23:28,866
[INDISTINCT TALKING]

586
00:23:33,800 --> 00:23:34,927
Ortho docs?

587
00:23:35,430 --> 00:23:36,759
BAILEY: Only louder!

588
00:23:37,268 --> 00:23:39,223
[POUNDING, WHIRRING CONTINUE]

589
00:23:40,590 --> 00:23:42,348
MEREDITH: Okay, you're
gonna feel a little pinch.

590
00:23:42,373 --> 00:23:44,123
It shouldn't hurt that bad, okay?

591
00:23:44,701 --> 00:23:45,701
That's it.

592
00:23:45,934 --> 00:23:47,637
- You good?
- Mm-hmm.

593
00:23:47,663 --> 00:23:49,833
Meredith, I was so sorry
to hear about Derek.

594
00:23:50,042 --> 00:23:52,542
Oh. Thanks. Me too.

595
00:23:52,567 --> 00:23:53,607
Who's Derek?

596
00:23:55,097 --> 00:23:57,259
I-It's a long story.

597
00:23:57,542 --> 00:23:58,825
[CELLPHONE CHIMES]

598
00:23:59,153 --> 00:24:00,153
Oh.

599
00:24:01,107 --> 00:24:02,633
This is for you.

600
00:24:03,542 --> 00:24:05,719
[GASPS] It's Farouk!

601
00:24:05,971 --> 00:24:06,971
Mm.

602
00:24:07,003 --> 00:24:08,337
He's a selfie master.

603
00:24:08,363 --> 00:24:09,571
[LAUGHTER]

604
00:24:09,596 --> 00:24:11,096
That's an impressive snout.

605
00:24:11,121 --> 00:24:13,202
- Yeah, excellent work.
- Where is he now?

606
00:24:13,825 --> 00:24:16,375
Ah, he's with U.S. Military in Baghdad.

607
00:24:16,500 --> 00:24:18,547
I haven't been able
to legally adopt him,

608
00:24:18,571 --> 00:24:20,077
and he's a Syrian refugee.

609
00:24:20,305 --> 00:24:22,383
It'll take years before
I can get him here, if ever.

610
00:24:22,715 --> 00:24:24,288
I just want to get back to him.

611
00:24:25,105 --> 00:24:26,683
Hey, Nathan, are you
planning on moving with...

612
00:24:26,684 --> 00:24:28,604
Megan, uh, looks like
you could use some air.

613
00:24:28,605 --> 00:24:30,064
Meredith, is it okay
if we take her outside?

614
00:24:30,065 --> 00:24:32,055
Oh, my God. Outside? Yes, please.

615
00:24:33,094 --> 00:24:35,104
- I got it! [LAUGHS]
- You all right?

616
00:24:35,105 --> 00:24:37,951
So this is what it
feels like to be a robot.

617
00:24:37,951 --> 00:24:38,976
[BOTH LAUGH]

618
00:24:39,000 --> 00:24:41,491
I don't know about robot.
I'm thinking more... alien?

619
00:24:41,517 --> 00:24:43,894
You think? Or, like,
strange sea creature, maybe?

620
00:24:43,894 --> 00:24:44,894
[SHRIEKING]

621
00:24:44,895 --> 00:24:46,433
There you go. That's it. That's it.

622
00:24:46,434 --> 00:24:48,601
- [SHRIEKING CONTINUES]
- [LAUGHS]

623
00:24:48,855 --> 00:24:50,763
You got a little weird when I asked

624
00:24:50,765 --> 00:24:52,469
about Nathan moving with Megan.

625
00:24:52,560 --> 00:24:53,917
You still upset with him?

626
00:24:56,474 --> 00:24:58,116
Nathan and Meredith were a thing.

627
00:24:58,407 --> 00:25:00,420
Right up until we got
the call about Megan.

628
00:25:00,876 --> 00:25:02,593
And we don't want her to know.

629
00:25:03,729 --> 00:25:05,344
Wait. Are you... Are you kidding?

630
00:25:05,835 --> 00:25:07,289
Owen, are you kidding me?

631
00:25:08,700 --> 00:25:11,569
Meredith is Megan's surgeon,
and you don't want her to know?

632
00:25:14,703 --> 00:25:15,897
You ready?

633
00:25:16,333 --> 00:25:18,108
Okay, you're gonna go to sleep now.

634
00:25:18,113 --> 00:25:20,112
When you wake up, you're gonna be...

635
00:25:20,113 --> 00:25:21,662
A warrior king!

636
00:25:21,663 --> 00:25:22,983
[LAUGHS] Exactly!

637
00:25:23,532 --> 00:25:24,571
Okay.

638
00:25:24,573 --> 00:25:25,797
[MONITOR BEEPING]

639
00:25:25,945 --> 00:25:27,866
All right. You're gonna do great, Max.

640
00:25:28,823 --> 00:25:30,101
[DOOR OPENS]

641
00:25:30,945 --> 00:25:32,593
RICHARD: And this is the O.R.

642
00:25:33,722 --> 00:25:35,707
Dr. Karev, mind if we observe?

643
00:25:35,873 --> 00:25:37,055
Um...

644
00:25:37,320 --> 00:25:38,976
It's up to you. It's your case.

645
00:25:39,413 --> 00:25:40,413
It's fine.

646
00:25:40,413 --> 00:25:41,272
Let's scrub.

647
00:25:41,298 --> 00:25:43,086
Okay, great. Let's go.

648
00:25:44,384 --> 00:25:45,686
Hey. Meredith?

649
00:25:46,113 --> 00:25:47,281
Meredith, you have a minute?

650
00:25:47,282 --> 00:25:48,155
Hi. Yeah.

651
00:25:48,181 --> 00:25:49,286
Did you read this article

652
00:25:49,310 --> 00:25:51,609
that Cristina published
on ex vivo lung perfusion?

653
00:25:51,634 --> 00:25:53,219
It's... It's not appropriate.

654
00:25:53,488 --> 00:25:55,111
To read Cristina's article?

655
00:25:55,366 --> 00:25:57,383
No, for you to operate on Megan Hunt.

656
00:25:57,407 --> 00:26:00,047
Oh. She chose the surgery.
She's aware of the risks.

657
00:26:00,071 --> 00:26:02,320
But she doesn't know about
your history with her fiancé.

658
00:26:02,346 --> 00:26:04,021
I mean, that's a serious
conflict of interest.

659
00:26:04,046 --> 00:26:06,045
You have to step away from this case.

660
00:26:06,069 --> 00:26:06,432
Well, I...

661
00:26:06,458 --> 00:26:07,523
You don't get to talk to her like that.

662
00:26:07,548 --> 00:26:08,718
- Amelia.
- Excuse me?

663
00:26:08,742 --> 00:26:10,522
- Okay, you're not Megan's doctor,
- Amelia.

664
00:26:10,548 --> 00:26:13,491
So if Meredith has decided that she
is equipped to handle a surgery,

665
00:26:13,492 --> 00:26:15,095
- you don't get to just show up here...
- I can fight my own battles.

666
00:26:15,118 --> 00:26:16,563
...like you own the place
and talk to her like that.

667
00:26:16,586 --> 00:26:17,616
I shouldn't have to.

668
00:26:17,663 --> 00:26:19,976
Megan is Owen's sister,
and you're Owen's wife,

669
00:26:20,000 --> 00:26:22,413
so I shouldn't have to
advocate for Megan and Owen,

670
00:26:22,439 --> 00:26:23,742
who have been through hell and back...

671
00:26:23,767 --> 00:26:25,211
a hell which I've personally witnessed.

672
00:26:25,236 --> 00:26:27,220
I shouldn't have to show up here
and advocate for them,

673
00:26:27,243 --> 00:26:28,351
because that's your job.

674
00:26:28,375 --> 00:26:30,680
But you're not doing it.
I have barely seen you.

675
00:26:30,704 --> 00:26:31,834
Because I have a patient.

676
00:26:31,858 --> 00:26:33,067
You also have a husband.

677
00:26:33,093 --> 00:26:35,751
I'm sorry. Is it 1952?

678
00:26:35,792 --> 00:26:38,462
Should I put on my apron
and mix him a gin and tonic?

679
00:26:39,211 --> 00:26:40,219
All right.

680
00:26:40,243 --> 00:26:42,992
It's not appropriate for you
to be Megan Hunt's surgeon...

681
00:26:43,018 --> 00:26:45,015
not when she doesn't have
the whole history.

682
00:26:47,782 --> 00:26:48,894
Who is she?

683
00:26:48,919 --> 00:26:52,413
That's... Owen's... person.

684
00:26:52,439 --> 00:26:53,689
I have a patient.

685
00:26:58,656 --> 00:26:59,945
Bovie.

686
00:26:59,947 --> 00:27:01,443
[EXHALES SHARPLY] Wow.

687
00:27:01,444 --> 00:27:02,905
That's more bands than I expected.

688
00:27:02,906 --> 00:27:04,786
RICHARD: Mind if we take
a closer look, Dr. Wilson?

689
00:27:04,787 --> 00:27:05,924
Be my guest.

690
00:27:05,925 --> 00:27:07,390
Okay. Uh, not you, Candace.

691
00:27:07,414 --> 00:27:09,805
Oh, and not you, either. Two at a time.

692
00:27:09,846 --> 00:27:12,608
I want you to see what
a malrotated bowel looks like.

693
00:27:12,634 --> 00:27:14,753
ALEX: Normally the Cecum
is in the right lower quadrant.

694
00:27:14,778 --> 00:27:16,448
JO: But in this case,
there are abnormal fibrous bands

695
00:27:16,471 --> 00:27:17,931
in the right upper quadrant,

696
00:27:17,955 --> 00:27:19,786
causing compressions of the duodenum.

697
00:27:21,497 --> 00:27:23,030
- [GASPS]
- [GASPS]

698
00:27:24,345 --> 00:27:25,644
LEVI: Oh, my God!

699
00:27:25,669 --> 00:27:27,367
- RICHARD: Oh, my God.
- JO: Oh, my God!

700
00:27:27,696 --> 00:27:29,144
♪♪

701
00:27:32,863 --> 00:27:34,326
ALEX: Step away from the table, Wilson.

702
00:27:34,349 --> 00:27:35,942
Dr. Karev, my patient, my surgery.

703
00:27:35,967 --> 00:27:37,567
Linda, sponge stick, please.

704
00:27:37,592 --> 00:27:38,882
Okay.

705
00:27:42,645 --> 00:27:44,315
JO: Okay, we're gonna need to change out

706
00:27:44,316 --> 00:27:46,015
the contaminated instruments
for new ones.

707
00:27:46,016 --> 00:27:48,308
We'll need antibiotic solution,
several liters.

708
00:27:48,334 --> 00:27:50,993
And, Dr. Webber, please remove
your students from my O.R.

709
00:27:52,739 --> 00:27:54,574
If you... don't mind, sir.

710
00:27:54,575 --> 00:27:56,903
I-Indeed, Dr. Wilson.
Let's go. Out, out.

711
00:27:56,904 --> 00:27:58,743
Let's go. Out, out, out! Out!

712
00:27:58,744 --> 00:28:00,903
- How's his pressure?
- Holding steady.

713
00:28:00,904 --> 00:28:02,904
Great. Irrigation, please.

714
00:28:06,051 --> 00:28:07,336
You paged Avery?

715
00:28:07,362 --> 00:28:08,532
Yeah. He's coming.

716
00:28:08,840 --> 00:28:09,903
When?

717
00:28:11,933 --> 00:28:13,644
Dr. Shepherd, have you slept?

718
00:28:15,161 --> 00:28:18,911
Well, you stand in this room
staring at this tumor,

719
00:28:18,935 --> 00:28:21,786
and I don't see you eat,
I don't know when you sleep.

720
00:28:22,480 --> 00:28:24,359
Look, I made a promise to this kid.

721
00:28:24,384 --> 00:28:26,540
And I made a promise to his father.

722
00:28:27,676 --> 00:28:30,346
Also, my husband's sister
came back from the dead,

723
00:28:30,346 --> 00:28:31,766
and my brother didn't.

724
00:28:31,767 --> 00:28:33,976
So... sleep is not really
my thing right now.

725
00:28:33,977 --> 00:28:35,136
[DOOR OPENS]

726
00:28:36,230 --> 00:28:37,935
Avery. Good.

727
00:28:37,936 --> 00:28:40,317
I'm thinking if we resect the tumor

728
00:28:40,342 --> 00:28:42,394
and reconstruct the jaw using
a portion of the temporal bone,

729
00:28:42,419 --> 00:28:43,509
we may be able to get ahead of...

730
00:28:43,532 --> 00:28:45,239
This is Kathleen Sampson.

731
00:28:45,378 --> 00:28:47,385
She was 17 when this picture was taken.

732
00:28:47,386 --> 00:28:49,636
And this... was her tumor.

733
00:28:50,109 --> 00:28:51,339
That look familiar?

734
00:28:51,989 --> 00:28:55,016
I did a sub-occipital approach
and a partial tumor resection,

735
00:28:55,017 --> 00:28:57,516
and then she looked... like that.

736
00:28:57,517 --> 00:28:58,739
But she was still in pain.

737
00:28:58,763 --> 00:29:01,045
I hadn't gotten the whole thing,
so it began to grow back.

738
00:29:01,355 --> 00:29:03,825
So I had to go in after it... again.

739
00:29:04,444 --> 00:29:05,911
Then again.

740
00:29:06,729 --> 00:29:08,479
You know what Kathleen looks like now?

741
00:29:10,181 --> 00:29:11,372
There's Kathleen.

742
00:29:14,336 --> 00:29:16,355
I'm not taking that boy's jaw apart.

743
00:29:17,386 --> 00:29:19,730
Please... stop summoning me.

744
00:29:22,886 --> 00:29:24,058
[KEYS CLACKING]

745
00:29:24,298 --> 00:29:26,067
[WOMAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY ON P.A.]

746
00:29:26,092 --> 00:29:27,464
[CELLPHONE BUZZING, CHIMING]

747
00:29:27,490 --> 00:29:29,325
- Dr. Webber?
- Ah. Karev.

748
00:29:29,333 --> 00:29:32,201
Uh, you know, I was very impressed
with how Wilson handled...

749
00:29:32,202 --> 00:29:34,541
A situation she never should've
had to handle? Yeah, so was I.

750
00:29:34,542 --> 00:29:36,461
We're here to talk about
the sub-I's, Dr. Webber.

751
00:29:36,462 --> 00:29:37,961
The utterly inept...

752
00:29:37,962 --> 00:29:39,291
Bottom-of-the-barrel med students

753
00:29:39,292 --> 00:29:41,523
you keep recklessly hauling
around the hospital.

754
00:29:42,833 --> 00:29:44,058
Oh, oh.

755
00:29:44,669 --> 00:29:47,378
So you two think you were
any better than them?

756
00:29:48,083 --> 00:29:50,894
Karev, you scraped in
by the skin of your teeth

757
00:29:50,920 --> 00:29:53,719
thanks to an essay you wrote
on testicular cancer...

758
00:29:53,743 --> 00:29:56,169
that I have since found was a lie!

759
00:29:56,942 --> 00:30:00,481
Kepner, you failed your boards
and got fired...

760
00:30:00,593 --> 00:30:01,722
twice!

761
00:30:03,051 --> 00:30:04,931
I raised you two.

762
00:30:05,019 --> 00:30:07,597
I grew you into the surgeons
you are now.

763
00:30:07,623 --> 00:30:10,741
So you don't get to tell me
